text: Aleksandr Lyubaturov (Russian: Александр Любатуров; born 4 April 1942) is a Soviet rower. He competed at the 1972 Summer Olympics in Munich with the men's coxed four where they came fourth. ==References== == External links == * * Category:1942 births Category:Living people Category:Soviet male rowers Category:Olympic rowers of the Soviet Union Category:Rowers at the 1972 Summer Olympics
